    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Frayed Tapestry</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John A Bacone letter on July 4 article deplores rapid rate of species extinctions</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The essay ''Lost Rivets and Threads, and Ecosystems Pulled Apart'' (July 4) likening the ''homogenization'' of earth's ecosystems to losing threads in a tapestry was thought-provoking and depressing. Not since major epochs of previous geologic eras has the earth seen such a rate of species extinctions, prompting some scientists to dub this the Homogecene. Unfortunately, it may be more appropriate to call it the Obscene Era.</p>
        <p>JOHN A. BACONE  Indianapolis</p>
      </block>
